next
  Summary: actor_can_hit, set_fire_queue_scale, reload events, is_reloading, reloading fire degrade, seen-class disclosure, is_monster_faction, get_section_npc_range, has_campfire offline, cell_key, make_trader, spawn_section, exclusive_spawn_section, exclusive_spawn_tiered

  xcombat
    - Added actor_can_hit(npc, cone_deg): true when the ACTOR could plausibly land a shot on the NPC -
      holds a firearm, facing within the cone, shot line clear (the actor-side mirror of fire_make_sense,
      built from the facing read + the target-capped ray). For exposure gates; pays a raycast, call on
      edges or feasibility checks, never per frame.
    - Changed set_combat's fire discipline: a FIRE/SNIPE intent degrades to READY while the NPC is
      reloading (new gate verdict "reloading"). A fire goal issued mid-reload cancels the engine reload,
      so periodic re-appliers were killing reloads over and over; the degrade lets the reload finish and
      fire resumes on the caller's next re-apply.
    - Changed set_combat: a SNIPE intent no longer enables the engine's sniper_fire_mode flag, and the
      takeover finalize no longer clears it. The flag replaces the fired direction with the sight's target
      angles and discards recoil (a non-converged shooter hits a target his model does not face), and is
      story-scene machinery vanilla combat never sets. SNIPE now means the sniper states alone: aimed pose,
      single shots on the state_mgr sniper cadence, normal direction and dispersion.
    - Added set_fire_queue_scale(npc, size_k, interval_k): per-NPC scaling of the combat planner's burst
      size and inter-burst interval (PR #603), probed and no-op on exes without the bind. Applies to
      vanilla-planner fire only; state_mgr fire states bypass select_queue_params.
    - Added on_reload_start(fn) and on_reload_stop(fn): registrars for the NPC weapon reload-edge
      callbacks (PR #611), probed and returning false on exes without the events. The stop edge is
      best-effort; bound edge-tracked state with a staleness window or confirm via is_reloading.
    - Added is_reloading(npc): authoritative reload read over the active weapon's state machine,
      works on every exe. The reload state numeric is 7 (eReload), not the 5 (eFire) circulating
      in older comparisons.
    - Changed disclose_enemy to also promote the disclosed enemy into SEEN memory on exes with the
      make_enemy_visible bind (PR #613, probed): enemy selection ranks "currently seen" far above hit
      memory, so the promotion is what makes the victim actually turn on the shooter. Floor exes keep
      the memory-only disclosure unchanged.

  xcreature
    - Added is_monster_faction(faction): true when a squad_descr faction string is a monster faction
      (monster_*, zoo_monster). Exposes the set get_mutant_species already used for its player_id fast reject.
    - Added make_trader(npc, cfg_path, stock_now): make an online NPC a functional shopkeeper from a
      vanilla trade config (trade_manager.trade_init + optional stock). Does not touch character_community,
      so faction-scoped trade systems keep seeing it. Sits next to is_trader / community / the money fns.

  xsmart_spawn
    - Added set_shared_spawn_section(smart, key, section, spawn_num): additive respawn_params inject of
      an explicit squad_descr section (vs the identity-to-pool set_shared_spawn), for injecting a
      specific squad (e.g. a service filler) into a smart's respawn.
    - Added set_exclusive_spawn_tiered(smart, key, faction, spawn_num): the exclusive faction inject
      with the squad tier read from the smart's own danger rung (spawn_all_weak fields novice squads,
      _normal novice/advanced, _hard advanced/veteran, _worst veteran only, per-smart _c_ variants
      matched by prefix). No rung declared falls back to the full 3-tier pool.
    - Added set_exclusive_spawn_section(smart, key, section, spawn_num): inject of an explicit
      squad_descr section tagged with the smart's owner faction so it passes the faction gate on an
      exclusive smart, where a plain shared-section entry (no .faction) would be suppressed. Passenger
      to an exclusive owner (reads smart.faction).

  xlevel
    - Added cell_key(level_id, position, cell_size): the shared density-cell partitioning ("level:x:z"
      at a caller-chosen cell edge, switch_distance by convention), so independent density consumers
      (culls, crowd gates) agree on what "the same area" means.

  xsmart
    - Added get_section_npc_range(section): both bounds of a squad section's npc_in_squad field, cached.
      Pairs with get_section_npc_max when the lower bound or the expected squad size is needed.
    - Changed has_campfire to consult a static map-campfire set first and fall back to the online table,
      so it answers offline map campfires once a consumer feeds the set via the new
      note_campfire_object(obj_name). Added campfire_map_count() for diagnostics.

1.8.2
  Summary: get_faction_smart_count, is_companion, is_unscriptable_se, dist_flat_sqr, set_combat fire discipline, fire queue bands, cover-repick veto

  xsmart
    - Added get_faction_smart_count(factions, level_id): count of smarts on a level with a
      stationed squad of the given community, or of any community in a given set. Reads the
      SIMBOARD squads roster through a per-level snapshot cached for 60 seconds.

  xsquad
    - Added is_companion(squad): true for an active companion squad, 0 luabind. The companion
      branch of has_active_role and is_protected now routes through it.

  xcreature
    - Added is_unscriptable_se: server-entity variant of is_unscriptable that works on offline
      entities. Checks story_id, unscriptable_npcs section, and squad story_id without a game
      object. The companion has_info signal is game-object-only and omitted.

  xcombat
    - Changed set_combat to take a fire intent plus the enemy and resolve the fire discipline
      itself: a FIRE or SNIPE intent degrades to READY when no shot makes sense. Consumers pass
      intent, not a resolved state, and hold no fire logic.
    - Added FIRE_QUEUE and get_fire_queue(kind, band): the engine's [fire_queue_params] burst
      envelope (size and interval bounds per weapon kind and distance band) as static data.
      Unknown kinds fall back to the rifle bands, unknown bands to medium.
    - Added on_cover_repick(fn): subscribe to the best-cover re-pick veto so fn(npc, flags) can set
      flags.allow = false to keep an NPC's current cover instead of shuffling to a newly-found one.
      Registers only when the engine seam exists and returns whether it did, inert on builds without it.

  xmath
    - Added dist_flat_sqr(a, b): squared ground-plane (XZ) distance, no sqrt, height-insensitive.

1.8.1
  Summary: xcombat engine fire-gate wrappers, xsmart roster reconcile, xsquad id snapshot, zero-consumer surface audit, xlog flush fix, mutant name localization, xmcm platform status

  xmcm
    - Added xmcm.platform_status: dynamic checking of xlibs and xray-monolith/AOEngine versions.

  xlog
    - Fixed the periodic flush firing exactly once per session instead of every 60 seconds.
      The flush timer now re-arms itself, so buffered INFO/DEBUG lines reach disk on the
      configured interval instead of waiting for a save, level change, or error write.

  xcreature
    - Changed get_name to translate-first for mutants: a localized inv_name or section string
      now beats the built-in English name table, and results are memoized per section.
    - Changed get_name to return nil for nil entities and nameless stalkers. Callers choose
      the fallback text (was baked "unknown" / "stalker" / "mutant").
    - Removed query() with its fluent iterator surface, entity_type, pos, online_iter,
      get_goodwill, set_goodwill. get_clsid is now internal. Zero consumers existed.

  xttltable
    - Fixed ttl_table :get() collapsing a stored false to nil. false now round-trips, matching
      the fifo_cache negative-cache convention.
    - Removed create_budget. Zero consumers existed.

  xsquad
    - Added collect_squad_ids(out): snapshots all SIMBOARD squad ids into a reusable array,
      id-only with zero luabind cost, so a caller can spread a squad walk across ticks without
      touching the live table mid-iteration.
    - Added create_squad(smart, section): spawns a squad at a smart through the vanilla board
      path, with roster assignment and squad_on_npc_creation fired natively.

  xcombat
    - Added wrappers over the per-NPC combat-AI engine binds from themrdemonized/xray-monolith
      PRs #594, #595, #596: set_aim_params, set_vision_speed, can_kill_enemy, can_kill_member,
      fire_make_sense, on_action_switch. Each wrapper probes its engine bind on the first call.
      Below the bind each degrades to a defined fallback, so consumers never touch a raw bind.
    - Added sees(npc, obj): the visible-right-now read (the test vanilla kill_enemy fires on),
      nil-guarded, so consumers route every sight check through one primitive.
    - Added get_cover_state(npc): the combat planner's stored cover flags (in_cover, looked_out,
      position_held) as one guarded read. Engine bookkeeping, not concealment geometry; returns
      nil when there is no planner to ask.
    - Added release_takeover_id(id): id-keyed sibling of release_takeover for server-side
      unregister, so a recycled NPC id re-grafts cleanly.
    - Changed install_takeover to assert on a second differing takeover spec instead of silently
      replacing the first consumer's policy. A failed install no longer writes the spec.
    - Removed resolve_stance, find_point, AGGRESSOR_KINDS. Zero consumers existed.
    - Fixed send_to returning the engine's invalid-vertex sentinel when accessible_nearest fails.
      It now falls back to the NPC's own node, so an arrival check cannot read the previous,
      already-completed path as an instant arrival.

  xsmart
    - Added reconcile_squad_roster(squad, from_smart_id): syncs SIMBOARD.smarts rosters after a
      squad changed smart through the roster-blind vanilla assign_smart, so has_capacity /
      is_smart_empty read truth. Idempotent, a no-op on a base that already syncs.
    - Fixed get_npc_roles serving a dead NPC's cached role set to the new holder of a recycled
      server id. Cache entries now verify the NPC section on hit and re-detect on mismatch.
    - Removed get_npc_for_job. get_declared_factions is now internal. Zero consumers existed.

  Surface audit
    - Removed every remaining export with zero consumers, verified by census across all 8
      consumer repos plus Warfare-erepb. Per-module lists below.
    - Removed from xtable: is_array, clone, filter, find, reduce, sweep, bisect_left,
      binary_insert, memoize, acquire_lock, check_lock, clear_locks.
    - Removed from xmath: chance, prd_chance, prd_reset, weighted_choice, vary.
    - Removed from xbus: unsubscribe, get_subscribers, count, has, stats, reset_stats, debug_state.
    - Removed from xevent: unhook, emit, list_hooks.
    - Removed from xinspect: inspect. get_type is now internal.
    - Removed from xtrace: wrap, reset. Removed from xprofiler: wrap.
    - Removed from xstash: is_stash_available, mark_stash_looted, clear_stash.
    - Removed from xlevel: get_game_hours, get_location_name.
    - Removed from xpda: hydrate_markers. Removed from xstring: capitalize_first.
    - Removed from xmcm: create_loader, extract_defaults, format_defaults, format_config.
      create_getter is now internal to create_config.

1.8.0
  Summary: xcreature get_clsid id-vs-clsid fix, invalid-entity sentinel cleanup, xsmart get_job_for_npc and is_near_campfire, xinventory get_rank_chance, release_item_id, create_item cond fix, xsquad get_community

  xcreature
    - Fixed get_clsid misclassifying low entity IDs. It short-circuited any number in [1,999] as an
      already-resolved class id and returned it unchanged, so early story NPCs (ids below 1000) read
      back their own id instead of a clsid and is_npc / is_stalker / is_mutant returned wrong answers.
      Numbers now always resolve through xobject.se. No caller passed a raw clsid through this path.
    - Replaced literal 65535 invalid-entity sentinels in get_mutant_species / get_mutant_variant with
      xconst.INVALID_ENTITY_ID, matching xsquad.

  xsmart
    - Added get_job_for_npc(smart, npc_id): the job a given NPC holds at the smart, or nil. Inverse
      of get_npc_for_job. The descriptor carries section and job_type_id.
    - Added is_near_campfire(smart, position, radius): true if the position is within radius of any
      campfire bound to the smart. Distinguishes a real fire seat from the campfire_point scheme's
      random-cover fallback.

  xinventory
    - Added get_rank_chance(section, actor, ruleset): a 0..1 appearance chance for a section by the
      actor's rank tier, with a hard category floor and per-tier cost bands. Rank-gate kernel for the
      AlifePlus faction market.
    - Added release_item_id(id): id-based sibling of release_item that releases offline items too
      (no game_object required).
    - Fixed create_item dropping the cond value on non-degradable items.
      alife_create_item registers the deferred set_condition only for use_condition sections, so
      weapons, outfits, and helmets spawned at full condition.
      create_item now applies the requested condition through alife_process_item for those sections.

  xsquad
    - Added get_community(squad): raw community id (faction key), the untranslated sibling of
      get_community_name.

1.7.7
  Summary: xcombat combat-AI module, xcreature goodwill, xpda npc tip, id-yielding iterator, xinventory policy rows by category or item section, dead-helper cleanup

  xcombat (new)
    - Combat-AI primitives for a script-driven NPC combat takeover: enemy-memory readers, ring-search
      cover and shot finders, a combat-state matrix, engine-routed movement and stance resolution, and
      disclose_enemy to force an NPC to register a known enemy. Drives the AlifeTactics turret takeover.

  xcreature
    - Added get_goodwill(obj, target) / set_goodwill(obj, value, target) over the engine personal
      relation registry. set_goodwill writes only the personal term (engine-clamped), letting a
      caller flip one NPC's attitude toward another without touching community relations.
    - Added online_iter_with_id() yielding (id, obj) pairs from gameobjects_registry (modded-exes)
      or db.storage (fallback). Caller can validate destroyed-state via alife_object(id) before any
      method call on obj, avoiding "you are trying to use a destroyed object [N]" warnings during the
      window where iterator yields an obj whose game-side destroy started but server release has run.

  xpda
    - Added npc_tip(npc, msg, opts) sending an NPC-attributed PDA tip: header is the speaker's name,
      body the message id, icon the speaker's portrait, plus a PDA sound. Direct to the actor (not
      faction-channel routed). opts: header, sound, showtime.

  xinventory
    - Added item-section policy rows: a policy row key is now a category or an item section. An item
      uses its section's rule when the policy names that section, otherwise its category's rule
      (policy_key); classify, iterate_surplus and build_surplus_map all key through it. A config can
      cap a whole category or single out individual items in one min/max policy.
    - Changed get_equipped_ids to exclude the grenade slot, so a slotted grenade stays managed by
      inventory policy (capped, or removed when its section is named) instead of reading as equipped.
    - Added is_corpse_take(mode, bag) and deny_move(flags) for ActorMenu_on_item_before_move
      handlers: is_corpse_take tells a loot-mode take from a dead body, deny_move vetoes the move.
      A consumer gates corpse looting without touching the engine list enum or the ret_value flag.
    - Removed get_ammo_count, get_ammo_classes, get_ammo_tier, get_ammo_tier_sorted. No downstream
      consumer remained after AlifeTactics at_ammo switched to a fixed AP section set. Public surface
      retains get_ammo_sections, get_ammo_tier_map (used by AlifePlus trade), resolve_ammo_category.

