1.7.5
  Summary: xinventory category API unified, runtime untouchable checks, multi-role NPC detection, xdata trader audit, smarts_by_names accessor

  xinventory
    - One category model now serves trade, stash, and inventory-balance LTX policy flows across mods.
      load_policy(path, sections, specials_set) loads any min/max-per-category LTX into { entries, rules, specials }.
      classify, iterate_surplus, build_surplus_map cover the count + surplus walks without per-consumer code.
      Section-side helpers: get_section_category, resolve_ammo_category, is_in_category, get_category_sections.
    - get_category(item, opts) adds 3 runtime untouchable checks (story_id, axr_companions, se_load_var "strapped_item").
      All consumers (trade, stash loot/fill, inventory-balance) inherit protection without per-consumer code.
    - LAST_MAIN_SLOT lowered from 18 to 14 to match runtime slot_persistent count (Inventory.cpp:72-86).
    - Removed 20 dedicated is_X predicates (is_medkit, is_bandage, ...); use is_in_category(sec, category) instead.
    - Removed in_reward_set. Superseded by the category model (get_section_category / is_in_category).
      (Record backfilled 2026-07-08, removal was in this release.)
    - Changed xobject.iterate_online_inventory to xinventory.iterate_inventory with the
      xobject/xinventory boundary split. (Record backfilled 2026-07-08, move was in this release.)

  xsmart
    - get_npc_roles(npc) returns the set of all roles an NPC fulfills (was get_npc_role single-string).
      Multi-role NPCs (Pripyat Yar = medic + trader, Petrenko/Sakharov = leader + trader) now report every role.
      level_spot signal dropped (vanilla quest scripts set level_spot=trader on non-traders).
      is_trader_npc, is_medic_npc, is_mechanic_npc unchanged (predicates over the set).
    - smarts_by_names() returns SIMBOARD.smarts_by_names for whole-world smart iteration (nil-guarded).
    - Removed get_controlling_faction (the 1.7.0 rename of get_smart_faction) and is_smart_hostile_to.
      Zero consumers remained. Holder reads go through smart.faction directly, props admission
      through accepts_faction. (Record backfilled 2026-07-08, removals were in this release.)

  xdata
    - 22 vanilla mechanics + 4 quest trader NPCs added to npc_roles as trader/medic destinations.
      Bar mechanic, army mechanics, Yantar techs, Jupiter techs (mechanics with dm_init_trader).
      Yantar cook, Kruglov, Jupiter nuclear physicist, Pripyat Yar (quest dialog hookups).
      Consumers reading xdata.traders now find every curated commerce destination.
    - Loris (esc_main_base_trader_mlr) faction corrected from army to stalker (loner trader at Cordon farm).
    - Explicit faction field on 4 Jupiter guard/leader entries (verified against squad_descr_jupiter.ltx).

1.7.1
  Summary: xsquad protection catches non-commander task-giver members; xsound one-shot helper for brief notification cues
  xsquad:
    Fixed: is_protected catches squads whose non-commander member is the task giver. _is_task_giver gained a pass 2: when no task points at the squad id or commander id, it accumulates task_giver_ids and matches them against squad:squad_members(). task_giver_id is polymorphic per vanilla (anomaly/axr_task_manager.script:723-732, sim_offline_combat.script:300-309): drx dialogs (axr_task_manager.script:792-794) write the squad id; vanilla dialogs.script:680 npc_give_task and iTheon PDA Taskboard (ui_pda_taskboard_tab.script:138) write the specific npc id of the selected member. Before the fix, the npc-id case only matched when the selected NPC happened to be the squad commander. Consumers (AlifeGuard, AlifePlus, AlifeBalance, TestZone) inherit the broader coverage on next call; no caller change required. Pass 1 cost unchanged; pass 2 fires only on pass-1 miss and adds one squad_members iteration with hash-set lookup.
  xsound:
    Added: play(snd_path, opts). One-shot 2D sound, no handle, no looping. For brief notification cues; pairs with the existing acquire/release looping API. opts.volume sets initial volume (default 1.0).

1.7.0
  Summary: faction-query surface trimmed and renamed to mark intent per question, tri-state smart hostility check, curated trader faction overrides
  xsmart:
    Added: is_smart_hostile_to(smart, community). Tri-state hostility check. Samples the first 3 npc_info entries; for each, resolves faction via xdata.npc_roles override then community() fallback. Returns true on first enemy seen, false when at least one faction resolved and none enemy, nil when no signal (offline, empty, or no faction resolved). Online + actor-level smarts only; caller layers a standalone-NPC cache for offline coverage.
    Renamed: get_smart_faction -> get_controlling_faction. Body changed: drops the iteration-order props fallback. Reads smart.faction (engine runtime set by check_smart_faction from NPCs at jobs) first, then smart.owning_faction when warfare set a real faction (skips the literal "none"), else "none". Unheld smarts return "none" so the caller can fall through to a post-arrival check.
    Renamed: get_smart_factions -> get_declared_factions. Name states the question (factions explicitly declared in smart.props LTX).
    Renamed: find_smarts_with_recipe -> find_smarts_spawning. Name states the question (smarts that spawn faction X on this level) instead of the implementation.
    Changed: is_smart_empty signature takes smart_id directly instead of smart. Matches the other SIMBOARD-indexing functions (get_smart_squads, has_squad_of_faction). Callers that previously passed smart now pass smart.id.
    Removed: accepts_mutant. Subset of accepts_faction, which dispatches the mutant branch via is_squad_monster automatically.
    Removed: has_faction, has_factions. find_smart and find_first_smart factions opt now matches via accepts_faction (engine Tier 1 with all / all_stalker / all_monster fallback). Behavior change at find_smart callers: smarts declaring all_stalker or all_monster now satisfy the factions filter.
    Removed: has_capacity. No live callers.
  xdata:
    Changed: npc_roles entries carry a faction field on every curated service NPC. Sidorovich-style universal-neutral traders get explicit faction encoding from lore (Petrenko at Dolg, Sakharov at Yantar, Ashot at Yanov, the Freedom leader at Army Warehouses, and the rest). Consumers reading get_npc_effective_faction see the curated override before falling back to engine community().

1.6.1
  xobject:
    Added: in_reward_set(sec, set_name). Section classifier reading itms_manager.item_rewards (parsed at module load from items\settings\item_rewards.ltx). Returns true if sec is listed under [set_name]. Sets shipping in vanilla Anomaly: items_health, items_bleed, items_rad, items_drink, items_food, items_medical, items_ammo, items_utility, items_money, items_grenade. Consumers gate item flow on vanilla-curated categories without duplicating section lists; addons that overlay item_rewards.ltx are picked up automatically.

1.6.0
  Summary: online inventory iterator centralized, generic NPC-by-job resolver, xstash notable filter removed
  xobject:
    Added: iterate_online_inventory(npc_id, callback). Centralized wrapper for NPC inventory walks. Returns the npc game_object when iteration ran, nil if offline or invalid. The explicit name carries the engine's online-only constraint into the API surface; offline NPCs are not an error case but a hard engine limitation (no Lua-side offline-inventory iterator exists). Callback signature matches engine convention; returning true stops iteration early.
  xsmart:
    Added: get_npc_for_job(smart, type_id). Returns the online game_object of the NPC assigned to a job of the given type_id at this smart. Generic resolver for assigned job slots (e.g. JOB_TYPE_CAMPFIRE_POINT, JOB_TYPE_GENERIC_POINT). Does NOT identify the trader NPC; job_type_id=15 (JOB_TYPE_TRADER) tags the visitor patrol slot (`<smart>_beh_trade_<i>`, gulag_general.script:971) rather than the barman's seated logic block.
  xstash:
    Removed: NOTABLE_PREFIXES, NOTABLE_SET, is_notable_item, filter_notable_stash_items. Domain-curated "which items are notable for news" filter that did not belong in a generic engine-wrap library. Zero callers outside xstash itself.

1.5.2
  Summary: per-level fast-path scans, squad gate reorder, gvid guard, section_faction cache, recipe primitives, xpp and xsound modules
  xsmart:
    Added: opts.source on find_smart and find_first_smart. Replaces SIMBOARD.smarts_by_names as the iteration pool when present; lets consumers inject a per-level bucket and bypass the global walk.
    Added: get_section_npc_max(section). Upper bound of a squad section's npc_in_squad field. Pairs with section_faction for recipe-content inspection. Cached.
    Added: find_smarts_with_recipe(level_id, faction). Walks SIMBOARD.smarts once, filters by level and by recipe-content match via section_faction. Returns smart server objects directly.
    Added: has_squad_of_faction(smart_id, faction, exclude_id). True if any squad of the given faction is at the smart; short-circuits on first match. Reads squad.player_id (trivial luabind) instead of get_squad_community (heavy).
    Changed: section_faction reads memoized per section. Repeated lookups for the same squad section return from cache instead of opening the LTX file each call.
  xstash:
    Added: opts.source on find_stashes. Replaces treasure_manager.caches as the iteration set when present; state (filled / looted / hidden) still read from treasure_manager.caches per iteration so mutations stay live.
  xsquad:
    Added: opts.source on find_squad and find_squads. Replaces SIMBOARD.squads as the iteration pool when present; lets consumers inject a per-level bucket and bypass the global walk. Symmetric with xsmart.find_smart and xstash.find_stashes.
    Changed: _squad_base_valid runs the level_id gate first. Wrong-level squads on level-scoped find_squads reject after one cached xlevel.get_level_id lookup (0 luabind warm) instead of paying position, npc_count, player_id reads first.
  xlevel:
    Fixed: get_level_id short-circuits on invalid m_tGraphID (engine sentinel GameGraph::_GRAPH_ID(-1) = 65535). Prevents an AV when callers pass position-less server objects. Required after the xsquad gate reorder, which now reaches get_level_id before the position check.
  xpp:
    Added: xpp module. Post-process effector wrap with slot allocator, engine-smoothed factor, and handle API. xpp.PPE table holds 35 verified-safe .ppe filenames tested in GAMMA.
  xsound:
    Added: xsound module. Looping sound wrap with handle API, Lua-side volume lerp, and lazy actor_on_update tick at 100ms.

1.5.1
  Summary: level adjacency, first-match smart lookup, faction acceptance check, squad-section faction lookup, commander rank, in-game clock, ttl_counter persistence, token bucket rate, offline cross-map item fallback
  xlevel:
    Added: get_level_id_by_name(name). Lazy name-to-level_id map from SIMBOARD.smarts_by_names.
    Added: get_neighbor_levels(source_id, hops). BFS over A-Life level adjacency; returns a set excluding the source. Cached per (source_id, hops). Powers off-map destination scans.
  xsmart:
    Added: find_first_smart(opts). First-match smart lookup with no ranking. Opts mirror find_smart factions / filter / level_id.
    Added: accepts_faction(smart, faction). True if smart's props admit the faction (stalker or mutant). Mirrors engine target_precondition Tier-1 admission gate. Use for routing-side decisions.
    Added: section_faction(section). Returns the player_id (faction community) a squad section will produce, reading the section's `faction` INI field from configs/misc/squad_descr/. Same string round-trips with squad.player_id at spawn and xcreature.community at runtime. Use to classify a smart's respawn_params.squads pool by what it spawns -- recipe-content checks for refill / spawn-intervention logic, where Tier-1 admission does not answer the question (props admit factions that recipes cannot produce, see doc/library/modding/smart-terrain-props.md).
    Removed: has_monster_jobs(smart, type_id). Constant-true predicate: gulag_general.init_monster_jobs pushes max_population*4 mob_home jobs (minimum 1) on EVERY smart (gulag_general.script:1018-1022), and load_jobs fills monster_jobs only for actor-level smarts (smart_terrain.script:457-464), so it never answered "can mutants go there". That question is accepts_faction (props admission) plus max_population (capacity). (Record backfilled 2026-07-08, removal was in this release.)
  xsquad:
    Added: get_commander_rank(squad). Commander rank; 0 for empty squads, non-stalkers, or unresolved commanders.
    Removed: is_squad_at_base(squad). No callers.
  xtime:
    Added: hms(). Returns the in-game hour, minute, second; nil when no level is present.
    Added: game_time(). Returns the engine's CTime userdata; nil when no level is present. Pairs with hms() for in-game wall-clock reads.
  xttltable:
    Added: ttl_counter :export() / :import(). Round-trips bucket state through save/load. Timestamps are clock-domain-specific (game_sec persists across save/load; os.clock does not).
    Added: token bucket :set_rate(rate). Updates refill rate without rebuilding; preserves in-flight token state.
  xobject:
    Changed: create_item offline cross-map fallback routes through alife_create_item with table owner instead of alife():create directly. Property table t is forwarded on this branch (t.ammo splits across boxes atomically at spawn; t.cond and t.uses queue via ItemProcessor with a ~0.16s drop window for offline carriers). Section non-existence is guarded; previously alife():create would Debug.fatal on missing sections.

1.5.0
  xchange:
    Added: xchange. Liquibase-style changeset registry for save-data migrations. Mods register changesets by globally-unique id and call run(m_data) from their LOAD_STATE handler. Each id runs once per save, recorded in m_data.xchange_log; subsequent loads skip applied changesets. register() warns on bad input or duplicate id. API: register(id, fn), run(m_data).
  xconst:
    Added: ACTOR_ENTITY_ID = 0. Engine convention for db.actor:id(). Pairs with INVALID_ENTITY_ID for actor-vs-other checks without magic numbers.
  xsmart:
    Added: has_jobs_for(smart, squad). True when every squad member has an engine-assigned job at the smart. Reads smart.npc_info[id].job per member; nil info or nil job returns false. Detects at arrival whether the engine allocated jobs (animation will run) or left members without slots (visible freeze case).
    Added: has_stalker_jobs(smart, type_id) and has_monster_jobs(smart, type_id) walk the matching job table; nil type_id matches any non-empty.
    Added: has_animated_stalker_jobs(smart). True on any non-stub stalker job_type_id (stubs are generic_point id=0, campfire_point id=1) and on any LTX exclusive job (job.exclusive=true, set by gulag_general add_exclusive_job). Use to filter smarts whose stalker_jobs[] holds only generic_point and campfire_point stubs (level designer authored no walker / guard / sniper / sleep / etc patrol paths).
    Added: JOB_TYPE_GENERIC_POINT, JOB_TYPE_CAMPFIRE_POINT, JOB_TYPE_MOB_HOME constants alongside the existing JOB_TYPE_TRADER and JOB_TYPE_MECHANIC.
    Removed: has_trader_job, has_mechanic_job, _has_job_type and the per-id caches. Callers use the parametric has_stalker_jobs(JOB_TYPE_TRADER) / has_stalker_jobs(JOB_TYPE_MECHANIC) form.
    Refactored: prop-flag predicates (is_base, is_lair, is_resource, is_territory, has_surge_shelter, is_smart_important) share a single _prop_truthy(smart, key) helper. Drops file CC under the 200-sum cap.
    Refactored: find_smart boolean preprocessing replaced and-or chains with explicit ifs (factions_check, min_dist_sqr, max_dist_sqr). Same behavior, lower CC.
    Fixed: set_shared_spawn and set_exclusive_spawn write squad-section tables into respawn_params[key].squads. _SQUADS_BY_IDENTITY now built with an explicit value-preserving merge of SQUADS_BY_FACTION and SQUADS_BY_SPECIES (xtable.merge is set-merge and was storing boolean true, which crashed vanilla try_respawn at smart_terrain.script:1677 when v["squads"][1] tried to index it).
  xsquad:
    Renamed: control_squad -> acquire_squad. Pairs with release_squad as acquire/release vocabulary; "control" was less specific than the multi-field engine acquire the function performs.
  xttltable:
    Added: create_budget(opts). Fixed-capacity counter with caller-managed reset. take / reset / remaining for per-tick or per-frame budgets. Pure-Lua O(1).

1.4.0
  Summary: Generic spawn injection API, level/smart name cascade, commander name resolver, weak-key species cache, cp1251-aware capitalize, fifo_cache iteration and on_evict
  xsmart:
    Removed: set_faction_controlled and clear_faction_controlled. Replaced by the generic spawn injection API below.
    Added: set_shared_spawn(smart, key, identity, num) and clear_shared_spawn(smart, key). Additive injection. Original LTX entries keep spawning alongside the injected entry. No faction filter applied.
    Added: set_exclusive_spawn(smart, key, identity, num) and clear_exclusive_spawn(smart, key). Faction-filtered injection. Sets faction_controlled + faction so only the injected entry spawns. Monster factions need periodic re-apply (engine check_smart_faction ignores monsters; smart_terrain.script:1209-1236).
    Added: SQUADS_BY_SPECIES table -- single-species simulation_<species> sections (20 entries) for species-pure mutant injection. Identity slot in the spawn API accepts both stalker factions and mutant species.
    Added: accepts_mutant(smart, player_id) mirrors the engine target_precondition mutant gate (props.all OR props.all_monster OR props[player_id]) at smart_terrain.script:1531-1532.
    Added: smart_iter() iterator over SIMBOARD smarts. Stateful, skips entries without a valid smrt ref.
  xlevel:
    Added: get_level_name(level_id) -- resolves a level_id to its localized display name via alife():level_name + game.translate_string.
    Changed: get_smart_display_name cascades Anomaly smart_names.ltx -> Warfare "st_<name>_name" key -> level display name -> cleaned raw section (previously returned raw LTX section on unnamed smarts). Every return path strips a recognized "Level. " prefix so "Zaton. Claw Anomaly Camp" becomes "Claw Anomaly Camp" regardless of source.
    Changed: get_smart_display_name returns nil on invalid input instead of the baked string "unknown". Callers decide the fallback. Keeps xlibs locale-pure.
    Changed: get_current_level_name returns nil when no level / no name is available, instead of the baked string "the Zone". Locale-pure, callers decide the fallback.
    Added: lazy session-cache of level names (raw + translated) used by the prefix-stripper.
  xsquad:
    Added: get_commander_name(squad) -- returns the commander's character_name. Hybrid resolver: tries online game_object via db.storage first (3 luabind fast path), falls back to cse_alife_trader_abstract:character_name() server-side binding (4 luabind, works for offline commanders). m_character_name is populated at NPC spawn and persists in saves; both paths return identical strings. Returns nil for empty squads, non-stalkers, and unregistered commanders.
    Changed: is_protected gained nil-squad and nil-opts early guards. Returns true,"nil_squad" for nil squads (fail-safe) and false for nil opts (no-criteria check) instead of erroring.
  xcreature:
    Changed: get_mutant_species and _resolve_npc_species now use weak-key per-entity caches. Repeat lookups for the same squad or NPC entity are 0 luabind after the first call. False sentinel stored for "resolved to nil" results so cache miss vs cached-nil are distinguishable.
  xstring:
    Added: capitalize_first(text) -- encoding-aware first-character capitalization. 256-byte uppercase table covers ASCII a-z, cp1251 Cyrillic а-я (0xE0-0xFF), and cp1251 ё (0xB8 -> Ё 0xA8). Replaces string.upper + %l regex, which are ASCII-only in Lua 5.1.
  xttltable:
    Added: fifo_cache :each(fn) iterates all cached values in insertion order (oldest first), and on_evict callback fires when a value is pushed out of the ring.
  xlog:
    Changed: defaults retuned. buffer_size raised from 1000 to 100000, flush_interval lowered from 300s to 60s. Larger in-memory buffer, faster periodic flush.

1.3.0
  xcreature:
    Added: online_iter() - safe game_objects_iter with db.storage fallback for vanilla/AOEngine
  Compatibility:
    Removed: modded exes requirement. Works with vanilla Anomaly 1.5.3, Demonized, Demonized MT, AOEngine. Tested with GAMMA, EFP, Zona.

1.2.7
  Summary: Species identification, squad control hardening, bounded cache
  xsquad:
    Added: reassert_target(squad, target) restores scripted_target if another mod overwrote it between scans.
    Changed: control_squad, target_actor, release_squad, reassert_target clear __lock (AP does not use it; scripted_target alone routes to specific_update).
    Fixed: fatal crash in _resolve_commander when non-squad server object arrives via squad_on_update callback (clsid guard in _check_permanent, field guard in _resolve_commander)
  xcreature:
    Added: get_mutant_species(input) returns the base species string for any entity. Accepts squads, server objects, game objects, or IDs. Handles modded exe clsid ambiguity via section prefix fallback. Stalker squads rejected at zero cost via player_id check.
    Added: get_mutant_variant(input) returns the full NPC variant section (e.g. "bloodsucker_red_strong").
  xttltable:
    Added: clock injection (opts.clock) for ttl_table, ttl_counter, token_bucket. Callers can pass game-time or custom clock functions. Default remains os.clock (zero luabind).
    Added: create_fifo_cache(opts) creates a bounded cache with ring buffer eviction. Oldest entry evicted when capacity is reached.

1.2.6
  Summary: Set operations
  xtable:
    Added: merge(...) - set union of hash tables. Variadic, nil-safe, returns new table.
    Added: subtract(base, ...) - set difference. Returns base keys minus all keys in remaining args.

